{"id":190860,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kurt_Eisner","text":"Kurt Eisner (14 May 1867 in Berlin \u2013 21 February 1919 in Munich) was a Bavarian politician and journalist. As a German socialist journalist and statesman, he organized the Socialist Revolution that took over the Wittelsbach monarchy in Bavaria in November 1918.\nHe is used as an example of \"charismatic authority\" by Max Weber.\nEisner was of Jewish descent.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Berlin","surface_form":"Berlin","offset":28},{"uri":"Munich","surface_form":"Munich","offset":57},{"uri":"Bavaria","surface_form":"Bavaria","offset":71},{"uri":"Politician","surface_form":"politician","offset":80},{"uri":"Journalist","surface_form":"journalist","offset":95},{"uri":"Germany","surface_form":"German","offset":112},{"uri":"Socialist","surface_form":"socialist","offset":119},{"uri":"German_Revolution","surface_form":"Socialist Revolution","offset":172},{"uri":"Wittelsbach","surface_form":"Wittelsbach","offset":212},{"uri":"Charismatic_authority","surface_form":"charismatic authority","offset":291},{"uri":"Max_Weber","surface_form":"Max Weber","offset":317},{"uri":"Jew","surface_form":"Jew","offset":342}]}